      "name": "good_prompt",
      "prompt": "Five friends (Alice, Bob, Charlie, David, Eve) are sitting in a row at a movie theater. Bob is sitting immediately to the left of David. Eve is sitting at one of the ends. Charlie is sitting somewhere to the right of Alice but to the left of Bob. Who is sitting in the middle seat? Let's think step by step, explicitly deducing the position of each person one by one before giving the final answer.",
      "response": "Let's break down the problem step by step.\n\n1. Eve is sitting at one of the ends, so she can only occupy either the leftmost or rightmost seat.\n\n2. Since Charlie is sitting to the right of Alice but to the left of Bob, Alice cannot be at the rightmost end (because Charlie would then be at the rightmost end, and there would be no room for Bob). So, Alice must be at the leftmost end.\n\n3. With Alice at the leftmost end, the order so far is: Alice,?,?,?,? (four seats remaining).\n\n4. Since Bob is sitting immediately to the left of David, and there is no one to their left, Bob and David must occupy the next two seats.\n\n5. The order now is: Alice, Bob, David,?,?.\n\n6. Charlie is to the right of Alice but to the left of Bob, so Charlie must occupy the next seat.\n\n7. The order is now: Alice, Bob, Charlie, David,?\n\nTherefore, the person in the middle seat is David.",
